italic&quot;&gt;No above ground new development shall commence until a detailed
overheating analysis assessment and overheating mitigation strategy is
submitted and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. Once
approved the strategy shall be implemented and permanently retained thereafter.
&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoListParagraphCxSpLast&quot; style=&quot;margin-left:18.0pt;mso-add-space:auto;
text-align:justify;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none&quot;&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11.0pt&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst&quot; style=&quot;margin: 0cm 0cm 6pt 18pt; line-height: 115%;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 115%;&quot;&gt;No above ground new development shall take place until
details of balconies and all materials to be used in the construction of the
external surfaces of the development have been submitted to and approved in
writing by the Local Planning Authority.&amp;nbsp;
The development shall be carried out in accordance with the approved
materials and balcony details.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;text-align:justify;mso-layout-grid-align:none;
text-autospace:none&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11.0pt&quot;&gt;Prior to commencement of
the development a vehicle access and egress strategy including details on how
the proposed layout can accommodated each vehicle type expected at the site,
traffic and parking management measures that may be necessary, detailed design
for access to and from the car parking and swept path analysis and turning
circles shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning
Authority . The approved strategy shall be implemented prior to first
occupation and retained for the lifetime of the development. &lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;text-align:justify;mso-layout-grid-align:none;
text-autospace:none&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;text-align:justify;mso-layout-grid-align:none;
text-autospace:none&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11.0pt&quot;&gt;Prior to commencement of
the development:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;text-align:justify;mso-layout-grid-align:none;
text-autospace:none&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11.0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt; text-indent: -18pt;&quot;&gt;(a) a dusk
emergence (or dawn re-entry) bat survey shall be submitted to and approved in
writing by the local planning authority. The survey shall&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt; text-indent: -18pt;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt; text-indent: -18pt;&quot;&gt;identify if bats are present on site.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;text-align:justify;mso-layout-grid-align:none;
text-autospace:none&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt; text-indent: -18pt;&quot;&gt;(b)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt; text-indent: -18pt;&quot;&gt;Should bats be present, a mitigation strategy
including details of roost replacement and working methodology to ensure no
bats are injured shall be prepared and submitted to the local planning
authority for written approval.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;text-align:justify;mso-layout-grid-align:none;
text-autospace:none&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt; text-indent: -18pt;&quot;&gt;(c)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 11pt; text-indent: -18pt;&quot;&gt;A bat licence will need to be acquired prior to the
demolition commencing.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;text-align:justify;mso-layout-grid-align:none;
text-autospace:none&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11.0pt&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

